				.recipe__main-info
					.recipe__item
						.acc-title 
							h2 INGREDIENTS
						.acc-body
							ul.recipe__ingredients 
								li 40 ml Broken Clock Vodka
								li 15 ml Pear Liqueur
								li 5 ml Graham’s No. 5 Port
								li 15 ml Apple Juice
								li 10 ml Lime Juice
								li 15 ml Earl Grey Syrup
								li 1 dash Plum Bitters
							.recipe__garnish 
								span Garnish
								ul 
									li Earl Grey Foam
									li Skeleton Leaf
					.recipe__item
						.acc-title
							h2 METHOD
						.acc-body
							.recipe__method 
								h3 For the Earl Grey Foam
								span Combine 250 ml Earl Grey Tea, 50 ml Vanilla Syrup, 1 tsp lecithin,   1 tsp sugar ester and add to a whipped cream syphon.
							.recipe__method 
								h3 For the Cocktail
								span 
									p Add all of the ingredients – other than the Earl Grey foam – to a Boston Tin along with plenty of ice and thoroughly shake until well chilled. 
									p Strain into a coupe before adding the foam using the syphon. For best results submerge the tip of the nozzle just below the surface of the cocktail. Finally perch the garnish on top before serving.
